research_name.thaumadditions:void_anvil=Void Anvil
research_stage.thaumadditions:void_anvil.1=WIP
Sometimes mundane anvils don't take long to break, that may be a bit frustrating. After studying void metal, I might try to cover the anvil with void metal. Perhaps that may improve lifespan of them!
research_stage.thaumadditions:void_anvil.2=WIP
Void metal seems to never stop impressing me, huh! I think this dark new anvil is pretty much infinite. But in exchance of damaging itself, it seems that every hit it gets, the aura pollutes by a little. I am going to need to be more careful next time!
##anvil w/ no durability, creates flux

research_name.thaumadditions:disenchant_fabric=Fabric of Disenchantment
research_stage.thaumadditions:disenchant_fabric.1=WIP
Enchanting items with mundane tools can be quite hard to alter, I will need a tool to let me take these enchantments and cast them back to (some) experience. Perhaps rubbing my tools with something soft yet magical?
research_stage.thaumadditions:disenchant_fabric.2=WIP
Enchanted Fabric along with salis mundus seem to provide a good and semi-reliable way of taking off the enchantments that I may have. The only catch here is the durability: the fabric seems to vanish after about 30 attempts. What a pain!
