research_name.thaumadditions:the_beheader=The Beheader
research_stage.thaumadditions:the_beheader.1=WIP
Every trip to the nether annoys me. Running around the fortress exhausting yourself and looking everywhere to find wither skeletons, hoping to get their skulls. Perhaps I should stop smashing those piles of bones and be actually careful enough to harvest black skulls?
research_stage.thaumadditions:the_beheader.2=WIP
Beheading seems like the way to go here. Improving on my thaumium axe would be an excellent idea - it fuses quite well with mithrillium. The new Beheader is lighter than an average axe, and has a good damage, so this may be used when I'm out of swords again.
## The Beheader - 11 attack damage, 20% behead chance.

research_name.thaumadditions:adaminite_sword=Adaminite Sword
research_stage.thaumadditions:adaminite_sword.1=WIP
While void metals posesses amazing powers, I have gone far in it's hierarchy, and I am confident that an upgrade to it is worthy.
research_stage.thaumadditions:adaminite_sword.2=WIP
Adaminite fuses well with it's own component, that's pretty smart. Though since adaminite is hard to apply, a lot of auxiliary essentia may be required. Adding some primal energy to it also makes this weapong a pretty much the best melee weapon any thaumaturge may posess. Or is it?
##Adaminite Sword - 16 attack damage, unlimited uses.

research_name.thaumadditions:mithminite_scythe=Mithminite Scythe
research_stage.thaumadditions:mithminite_scythe.1=WIP
Mithminite has proven to be quite important in few ways, but perhaps a tool could be made out of it?
research_stage.thaumadditions:mithminite_scythe.2=WIP
Unfortunately, just putting Mithminite on a tool handle is a bad idea - all rods that I've tried break very fast... Though it seems like making the entire tool out of mithminite with help of some auxiliary materials is possible, and the result may be a bit more deadly then I expected... Somehow the new scythe is able to shoot with phantom scythes that are also a bit more strong then mine. Oh well, might as well go and murder some enemies.
